<h1 class="entry-title" style="text-align: center"><b>In The Not So Distant Future, Glow-In-The-Dark Trees Could Replace Street Lights</b></h1>



<div class="td-module-meta-info">
<div class="td-post-author-name"><div class="td-author-by">By</div> <a href="">Katherine Brooks</a><div class="td-author-line"> ---------- </div> </div>                   
<span class="td-post-date"><time class="entry-date updated td-module-date" datetime="2020-11-27T09:56:03+00:00">
    April 2, 2014 </time></span>                                                        </div>

</header><br>

</div>

<div class="td-post-sharing-top"></div>

<div class="td-post-content">

<div class="td-post-featured-image"><a href="https://dogstodaymagazine.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Roxi-parcel-dog-copyright-Vets-Now-1-scaled-e1606470770170.jpg" data-caption="" class="td-modal-image"></a></div>
<div class="cli cli-embed js-no-inject"><div class="cli-embed__embed-wrapper"><script type="text/javascript">try{ var src_url="https://spshared.5min.com/Scripts/PlayerSeed.js?playList=518180003&height=381&width=570&sid=577&origin=undefined&videoGroupID=148829&relatedNumOfResults=100&relatedMode=2&relatedBottomHeight=60&companionPos=&hasCompanion=false&autoStart=false&colorPallet=%23FFEB00&videoControlDisplayColor=%23191919&shuffle=0&isAP=1"; src_url += "&onVideoDataLoaded=HPTrack.Vid.DL&onTimeUpdate=HPTrack.Vid.TC"; if (typeof(commercial_video) == "object") { src_url += "&siteSection="+commercial_video.site_and_category; if (commercial_video.package) { src_url += "&sponsorship="+commercial_video.package;  } } document.write('<scr' + 'ipt type="text/javascript" src="'+src_url+'"></scr' + 'ipt>');}catch(e){}</script><script type="text/javascript" src="https://spshared.5min.com/Scripts/PlayerSeed.js?playList=518180003&amp;height=381&amp;width=570&amp;sid=577&amp;origin=undefined&amp;videoGroupID=148829&amp;relatedNumOfResults=100&amp;relatedMode=2&amp;relatedBottomHeight=60&amp;companionPos=&amp;hasCompanion=false&amp;autoStart=false&amp;colorPallet=%23FFEB00&amp;videoControlDisplayColor=%23191919&amp;shuffle=0&amp;isAP=1&amp;onVideoDataLoaded=HPTrack.Vid.DL&amp;onTimeUpdate=HPTrack.Vid.TC"></script></div></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>According to Daan Roosegaarde, the future of art and design is awash with spectacular innovation. </p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>From <a href="https://www.huffpost.com/entry/daan-roosegaarde_n_4163920" target="_hplink" role="link" class=" js-entry-link cet-internal-link" data-vars-item-name="giant vacuum cleaning systems" data-vars-item-type="text" data-vars-unit-name="5bb26d32e4b0171db6a0a348" data-vars-unit-type="buzz_body" data-vars-target-content-id="https://www.huffpost.com/entry/daan-roosegaarde_n_4163920" data-vars-target-content-type="buzz" data-vars-type="web_internal_link" data-vars-subunit-name="article_body" data-vars-subunit-type="component" data-vars-position-in-subunit="0">giant vacuum cleaning systems</a> aimed at eradicating smog to <a href="http://designtaxi.com/news/363997/A-Futuristic-Dress-That-Becomes-Transparent-When-You-Get-Turned-On-NSFW/" target="_hplink" role="link" class=" js-entry-link cet-external-link" data-vars-item-name="&quot;smart&quot; apparel " data-vars-item-type="text" data-vars-unit-name="5bb26d32e4b0171db6a0a348" data-vars-unit-type="buzz_body" data-vars-target-content-id="http://designtaxi.com/news/363997/A-Futuristic-Dress-That-Becomes-Transparent-When-You-Get-Turned-On-NSFW/" data-vars-target-content-type="url" data-vars-type="web_external_link" data-vars-subunit-name="article_body" data-vars-subunit-type="component" data-vars-position-in-subunit="1">"smart" apparel </a>that becomes translucent when the wearer is turned on, the Dutch artist/designer/architect has helped imagine some hair-raising projects that could propel us into a new era of aesthetics. </p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>His newest endeavor -- a plan to replace light fixtures with bioluminescent plants -- is no letdown in comparison.</p></div>

<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>Taking a cue from biomimicry, Roosegaarde is hoping to transform your average street-side trees into beacons of light for passersby. Like the luminescent abilities of jellyfish, mushrooms or fireflies, Roosegaarde, scientist <a href="http://bioglowtech.com/about.html" target="_hplink" role="link" class=" js-entry-link cet-external-link" data-vars-item-name="Alexander Krichevsky" data-vars-item-type="text" data-vars-unit-name="5bb26d32e4b0171db6a0a348" data-vars-unit-type="buzz_body" data-vars-target-content-id="http://bioglowtech.com/about.html" data-vars-target-content-type="url" data-vars-type="web_external_link" data-vars-subunit-name="article_body" data-vars-subunit-type="component" data-vars-position-in-subunit="2">Alexander Krichevsky</a> and the State University of New York are all on the case, splicing DNA from luminescent marine bacteria with the chloroplast of a houseplant. </p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>The smaller-scale, glow-in-the-dark specimens would act as the basis for a project of greater proportions -- light-emitting installations that look like trees. "What happens when technology jumps out of the computer screen and becomes part of the things that we wear and the roads that we drive on?" Roosegaarde muses in the video above.</p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p>Watch the short clip to hear the artist speak more about his ambitious plans and the reason he's ventured to the United States to pursue his quest. Let us know your thoughts on the merging of nature and technology in the comments.</p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p><a href="http://www.dezeen.com/2014/03/24/movie-sxsw-daan-roosegarde-glow-in-dark-trees/" target="_hplink" role="link" class=" js-entry-link cet-external-link" data-vars-item-name="h/t Dezeen" data-vars-item-type="text" data-vars-unit-name="5bb26d32e4b0171db6a0a348" data-vars-unit-type="buzz_body" data-vars-target-content-id="http://www.dezeen.com/2014/03/24/movie-sxsw-daan-roosegarde-glow-in-dark-trees/" data-vars-target-content-type="url" data-vars-type="web_external_link" data-vars-subunit-name="article_body" data-vars-subunit-type="component" data-vars-position-in-subunit="3">h/t Dezeen</a></p></div>
<div class="primary-cli cli cli-text "><p><em>Correction: An earlier edition of this article stated Roosegaarde employed biomimicry in his work. The piece has been amended to clarify he was inspired by it. </em></p></div>
</div>


